Package: heterovar
Title: Generation of data from a joint model including heterogeneous variability
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Antoine", "Barbieri", , "antoine.barbieri@u-bordeaux.fr", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5226-5631"))
    person("Léonie", "Courcoul", , "Léonie.Courcoul@u-bordeaux.fr", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5226-5631"))
Description: heterovar allows to generate dataset from a joint model for longitudinal and time-to-event data. Note that longitudinal data are generated from a linear mixed model including time-dependent and subject-specific variability for measurment errors. The risk to develop the event depends of both the current value and current variability of longitudinal marker. 
